Interface PrimitiveList

All Superinterfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.DoubleQuantizable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Quantizable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection.Sized, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.Stringable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.StringSource

All Known Implementing Classes:
ByteArray, CharArray, IntArray, IntListAdapter, LongArray, PackedArray, ShortArray, SplitByteArray, SplitCharArray, SplitIntArray, SplitLongArray, SplitPackedArray
public interface PrimitiveList extends com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection.Sized
Interface implemented by primitive lists. Primitive values are treated as longs to unify the different lists and allow them to be treated the same.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
